1989 — KR580VM1 (КР580ВМ1)

Created in the USSR by the State Committee for Electronics Technology; Ministry of Electronics Industry, it is mostly compatible with the Intel 8080 and includes some of the undocumented instructions from the Tundra CA80C85B.

Address space
Two banks of 16-bit
I/O space
8-bit
1 0 1 0
PSW A F
B B C
D D E
H H L H1 H1 L1
SP SP
PC PC
7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 0
F S Z OF AC MF P 1 C IE IE

Main table

  • Green marks new instructions to the Intel 8080.
  • Red marks new instructions replacing earlier ones for the Intel 8080.
  • Orange marks instructions present but undocumented in Intel 8080 and documented for the KR580VM1 (КР580ВМ1).
  • Pink background marks undocumented instructions.
  • Plum background marks duplicate instructions.
